How to Run the Application
To successfully run this application, you must run the backend server and the frontend UI simultaneously in two separate terminal windows.

 Prerequisites
Before running, ensure you have your secure .env file created in the root directory. It should contain your MongoDB connection string:
MONGO_URI=mongodb+srv://<username>:<password>@cluster0...

 Terminal 1: Start the Backend Server
This terminal keeps the pipeline to the MongoDB cloud wide open.

Open your terminal in the root ExerciseApp folder.

Activate your virtual environment:

Bash
.\\venv2\\Scripts\\Activate.ps1
Boot up the FastAPI server:

Bash
py -m uvicorn server:app --reload
Status: The server is now listening for requests at http://127.0.0.1:8000.

📱 Terminal 2: Launch the Frontend Application
This terminal launches the actual visual window.

Open a new, separate terminal tab.

Activate your virtual environment again (every new terminal needs activation):

Bash
.\\venv2\\Scripts\\Activate.ps1
Run the CustomTkinter UI script:

Bash
py appbd.py
Status: The graphical user interface will open, allowing you to select equipment and muscle groups to query the live cloud database.
"""

